The paper discusses a framework for robot perception, real-world modelling, and navigation, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The framework uses a stochastic tesselated representation of spatial information, which involves probabilistic estimates and Bayesian estimation mechanisms, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG). The paper also discusses path-planning and obstacle avoidance, which are common topics in control systems (cs.SY).
